article.description: Desmond Williams and Marcus Barham scored 17 points apiece and Florida A&M beat Johnson University 100-91 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Florida A&M beats Johnson University 100-91
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. -- Desmond Williams and Marcus Barham scored 17 points apiece and Florida A&M beat Johnson University 100-91 on Thursday night. Florida A&M has scored 194 total points in its past two games -- both wins -- and topped 100 points for the first time since the season opener last season against Johnson. Craig Bowman added 16 points and Justin Ravenel had 15 points for Florida A&M (2-1). Bowman made four 3-pointers and the Rattlers hit 11 of 20 -- with eight in the second half. Josh Grover led Johnson with 25 points, nine rebounds and seven assists. Kendall Oliver added 22 points, and Duane Howard and Caleb Winfrey had 13 points each. The Suns made 58.9 percent (33 of 56) of their field goals but turned it over 27 times. Johnson is a member of the National Christian College Athletic Association.
